<plot>On The Lake: Life and Love in a Distant Place tells the true story of the tuberculosis epidemic in America in the 1900s and globally today through the lives of those that were infected and who died -- but also of those who survived. More than scientific facts and figures, On The Lake touches that rare emotional cord of what life was like for millions of people infected with TB, while providing a glimpse into human nature when faced with a large-scale epidemic.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?411188</url></doc>
